                    </svg>
                    The Origin Story
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-3">
                    HugeVoice was born from a simple but frustrating problem we've all experienced: being at the back of a crowd and never being able to hear what folks are saying at the front. During a conversation with friends about this universal struggle, <strong>Mark Davis</strong> had a brilliant insight:
                </p>
                <blockquote class="blockquote border-start border-primary border-4 ps-3 mb-3">
                    <p class="mb-0">"We could use their phones as speakers and allow folks to jump on the channel using QR codes."</p>
                    <footer class="blockquote-footer mt-2">Mark Davis</footer>
                </blockquote>
                <p>
                    This idea sparked something bigger - a conversation about what the <strong>post-platform internet</strong> should look like. A world where technology serves people directly, without corporate intermediaries controlling the flow of information.
                </p>
